This paper is about a real-time instance segmentation model that achieves competitive results on MS COCO. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of deformable convolutions, which are commonly used in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a fast mask re-scoring branch, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category.
